			<ns0:name>cstefan...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/113511172007743761909/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">If the nexe or sel_ldr crashes, the NaCl canvas in the renderer will freeze or just be a white rectangle.

This is unfortunate, because the user has no way of knowing why the content is not being rendered.

Proposal: Show an unhappy smiley with a message like &amp;quot;Something went wrong while displaying this content. To continue, reload or go to another page. Learn more.&amp;quot; where &amp;quot;Learn more&amp;quot; links to a Help Center article. (See the current about:crash page for inspiration.)

We'll need UI design, string localization, and plumbing for the crash detection.
